The package @swapdk/wdk-wallet-cosmos is a fork of @base58-io/wdk-wallet-cosmos
(https://github.com/base58-io/wdk-wallet-cosmos), licensed under Apache 2.0.
Modifications by SwapDK add support for THORChain (RUNE) and MAYAChain (CACAO)
swap-deposit messages, which the upstream package does not currently expose.

The package @swapdk/wdk-wallet-btc is a fork of @tetherto/wdk-wallet-btc
(https://github.com/tetherto/wdk-wallet-btc), licensed under Apache 2.0.
Modifications by SwapDK add optional `memo` support on `sendTransaction`,
`signTransaction`, `quoteSendTransaction`, and `getMaxSpendable`, emitted as
an OP_RETURN output (≤80 bytes). Required for THORChain / MAYAChain inbound
observation, which routes on the OP_RETURN payload of the BTC deposit.

The package @swapdk/wdk-wallet-tron is a fork of @tetherto/wdk-wallet-tron
(https://github.com/tetherto/wdk-wallet-tron), licensed under Apache 2.0.
Modifications by SwapDK add optional `data` (raw hex calldata) and `feeLimit`
(SUN cap on energy) to `sendTransaction` and `signTransaction`. When `data`
is supplied, the wallet emits a `TriggerSmartContract` with the calldata
verbatim (via tronweb's `input` option on `triggerSmartContract` with an
empty function selector). Required for invoking the THORChain router's
`depositWithExpiry(...)` from TRON, which the upstream's hardcoded TRC-20
`transfer(address,uint256)` and plain TRX `sendTrx` paths cannot construct.

